Regardless of fortification, milk is an extremely nutritious food. Vitamin A and D supplements are added as a result of fortification. In most cases, these vitamins are not found in milk. Fortification is the process of adding these vitamins to milk. "Fortified milk helps with eye health and calcium absorption more than ordinary milk," she explains. Picky eaters exist in both children and adults. This could have an impact on bone health. Vitamin D improves calcium absorption and promotes strong bones. As a result, fortified milk with added nutrients encourages us to have a well-balanced diet.
